caller_intent: The caller needs to update their insurance policy by removing a totaled vehicle and adding a new car, as they recently purchased a replacement after an accident. They are concerned about returning license plates to avoid fines and ensuring the new vehicle is properly insured.
resolution_steps: Agent clarifies they cannot handle the request immediately and will connect the caller with an agent.
Agent provides their contact number for follow-up.
Agent suggests the caller may visit the office in person if they prefer.
knowledge_required: DMV requirements for vehicle registration and license plates
Handling totaled vehicles and policy adjustments
systems_referenced: Alliance Insurance internal policy management system
summary: A caller contacted Alliance Insurance to update their policy after a car accident, needing to remove a totaled vehicle and add a new car. The agent explained they would connect the caller with an agent for further assistance and suggested visiting the office if needed. The call ended with a promise to follow up.
